    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02008.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Low Gap. Mendocino Co.,</name>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">California</name>
                    <date when="1877-08-02" rend="right">Aug. 2. 1877<ptr target="loc.02008_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Walt Whitman</salute>
                <salute>My beloved.<ptr target="n0835"/></salute>
            </opener>

            <p>A pioneer in the redwood forest salutes you, greets you with love sincerest and best. embraces you with her whole being, as the one chief among men and altogether lovely.</p>
           
            <q who="Walt Whitman"><lg><l>"This is no book</l>
                <l>Who touches this, touches a man"</l></lg></q>
                <p>I feel it. I know it.</p>
                               
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02008.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.02008.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            
            <p>Nothing that I ever read so filled me with joy and gladness</p>
            
            <p>Sitting solitary in the forest, bathed in the warm sunlight with the cool breeze whispering to me, I know that we are akin and am thankful. I take the kiss you give. I know it was especially for me</p>
            
            <p>You will take my kisses and love as from me that knows you and can never forget you</p>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.02008.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="loc.02008.005_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            
            <p>I have received so much that I must make some return be it ever so little.</p>
            
            <p>John Burroughs<ptr target="n0129"/> more than <choice><orig>any one</orig><reg>anyone</reg></choice> that I know, fitly expresses my thought of you. I love him for it.</p>
           
            <p>I have never met <choice><orig>any one</orig><reg>anyone</reg></choice> that seemed to have the faintest understanding of you so I keep you all to myself locked in my heart of hearts.</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Kate A. Evans.</signed>
            </closer>
             
            <pb xml:id="leaf003v" facs="loc.02008.006_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf004r" facs="loc.02008.007_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ww" place="left">from the Californian Kate Evans (? rather gushing)</note>
            <pb xml:id="leaf004v" facs="loc.02008.008_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        
